{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so that the summary can attribute statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure is not just local parsing logic; it depends on real diarization quality from the speech-to-text model on real audio. A mocked transcript can hide speaker-label loss/misattribution that appears with actual model output. This is a single agentic dependency, not a multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run the service on real multi-speaker meeting audio through the real speech-to-text API, then generate the summary and verify attendee attributions match known speakers in the recording; fail if labels are dropped, swapped, or collapsed to unknown speaker.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.45,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The structured summary contains at least one action item for every attendee who was assigned a task during the meeting.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on LLM extraction/attribution quality, which varies by model behavior and prompt sensitivity. Mocking the LLM would likely pass and hide real misses where assigned tasks are omitted for some attendees. This is one agentic step, not a multi-step workflow requirement.","test_description":"Provide transcripts with known attendee-task assignments to the real summarization model and assert the structured output includes at least one action item per assigned attendee; run multiple trials and fail on omissions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions mentioned in the transcript appear in the \"decisions\" section of the summary, not buried in the narrative.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The core risk is semantic extraction and section placement by the LLM. Module wiring tests alone cannot prove decision capture quality or structured placement fidelity. A mocked model response would hide this failure mode.","test_description":"Use transcripts containing explicit decision statements, call the real summarization model, and assert those decisions are present in the dedicated \"decisions\" field/section (not only free-text narrative).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"The failure boundary is a multi-step sequence: segmentation, repeated transcription/summarization across chunks, and final merge coherence. Bugs often emerge only across step handoffs (ordering, context loss, duplication), and mocking can hide cross-step degradation. This requires validating a real agentic sequence, not a single call.","test_description":"Run a real >60-minute meeting recording through the full chunking path, verify each segment is processed in order, and validate the merged final summary is coherent and non-duplicative with preserved cross-segment action items/decisions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.5}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output — completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly targets end-to-end autonomous execution across multiple dependent stages, including agentic model calls. Real failures arise from stage orchestration, retries/timeouts, schema handoff, and final delivery integration; lower-level tests can miss these emergent failures.","test_description":"Execute an end-to-end run with a real meeting recording: upload, real transcription, real summarization, and output delivery. Assert completion without human fixes, valid structured schema, and successful final artifact delivery.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
